dspace-development.title: Downloads for DataSpace Bundle 159270 are failing

comments.body:
This is related to a file-system level permissions issue:

```bash
2021-09-20 14:49:54,348 ERROR org.dspace.app.webui.servlet.DSpaceServlet @ jrg5@princeton.edu:session_id=9273DD094D273CA64C419930DC15BCF7:ip_ad
dr=137.83.219.136:unhandled error:java.io.FileNotFoundException\colon; /mnt/disks/dataspaceproddatastore/prod-copy/assetstore_production/13/49/
66/134966057684743006473428354266837213174 (Permission denied)
java.io.FileNotFoundException: /mnt/disks/dataspaceproddatastore/prod-copy/assetstore_production/13/49/66/1349660576847430064734283542668372131
74 (Permission denied)
        at java.io.FileInputStream.open0(Native Method)
        at java.io.FileInputStream.open(FileInputStream.java:195)
        at java.io.FileInputStream.<init>(FileInputStream.java:138)
        at edu.sdsc.grid.io.local.LocalFileInputStream.open(LocalFileInputStream.java:171)
        at edu.sdsc.grid.io.GeneralFileInputStream.<init>(GeneralFileInputStream.java:145)                                                             at edu.sdsc.grid.io.local.LocalFileInputStream.<init>(LocalFileInputStream.java:139)
        at edu.sdsc.grid.io.FileFactory.newFileInputStream(FileFactory.java:630)
```

This was resolved by manually updating the owning user:

```bash
$ sudo chown -R dspace:dspace /mnt/disks/dataspaceproddatastore/prod-copy/assetstore_production/13/
```

dspace-development.title: Does anyone offer symplectic as SAAS?

comments.body:
Digital Science is the vendor that provides Symplectic Elements software licenses to customers, and also offers Symplectic as a hosted service.  According to the [vendor website](https://www.symplectic.co.uk/solutions/servicesandsupport/), the service includes: 

* Regular upgrades of Elements software
* Server availability and maintenance 
* Data migrations

Next steps: determine if any workflows are custom workflows that would require something other than what the hosted solution can provide; investigate cost.

The HR People feed feature is core to Elements, non-customized:

* https://support.symplectic.co.uk/support/solutions/articles/6000126041-how-to-install-the-elements-standard-hr-importer

Test index took ~ 21 hours and failed to index 4 things.
```
E, [2021-09-18T00:14:31.938747 #27746] ERROR -- : Could not index bdbba79d-72c1-4238-ba69-99c741dd00a5 due to RSolr::Error::Http
E, [2021-09-18T00:14:31.969881 #27746] ERROR -- : Could not index 0fb4f29c-547c-4ec4-a9c6-bc47cf43c742 due to RSolr::Error::Http
E, [2021-09-18T00:14:32.360729 #27746] ERROR -- : Could not index 39f13dcd-247d-46bf-bc2e-40e7949c3c4d due to RSolr::Error::Http
E, [2021-09-18T00:14:45.806319 #27746] ERROR -- : Could not index 392e0a93-b15d-46b9-8b8f-249c7f217de5 due to RSolr::Error::Http
```

The broken ones were all items with bad nested objects, probably from an old bad ingest. I adjusted them in the interface by manually selecting the vocabularies that had the same nested labels - they were all the same, which points towards them being from the same ingest.
